    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\n`z=` without a count delegates spell suggestions to `vim.ui.select()`.\r\nPicker implementations such as fzf-lua may keep focus in a transient window,\r\nso `curwin` can change before `spell_suggest()` unwinds.\r\n\r\nThe cleanup path restored the saved cursor and temporary `'spell'` state through `curwin`.\r\nWhen `curwin` is the picker window, that can leave the picker with a cursor line\r\nthat is valid in the spelling buffer but invalid in the picker buffer.\r\nA later redraw or buffer access can then emit `E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum`.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nSave the window and buffer that started `z=`.\r\n\r\nRestore temporary `'spell'` before handing off to the picker,\r\nso picker-side buffer switches cannot save that temporary state into window-local options.\r\nRestore the saved cursor only when the original window still shows the original buffer.\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\n- `CCACHE_DISABLE=1 TEST_FILE=test/functional/lua/ui_select_spec.lua TEST_FILTER=\"changes its buffer\" TEST_TIMEOUT=60 cmake --build build --target functionaltest`\r\n- `CCACHE_DISABLE=1 TEST_FILE=test/functional/lua/ui_select_spec.lua TEST_FILTER=\"via z=\" TEST_TIMEOUT=60 cmake --build build --target functionaltest`\r\n\r\n## AI assistance\r\nAI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\nThe patch was generated by Codex. I have not reviewed it yet, so leaving the PR as draft for now.\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If this feels like a treadmill where we're going to be patching stuff up endlessly, maybe a simpler approach is to just divert the `[count]` case to a synchronous path. E.g. the lua code will just call `inputlist()` in that case.\r\n\r\nOr we can try the approach here and retreat to `inputlist()` if we keep finding problems.",
